docs.text: not since 1996's shine , which starred geoffrey rush as pianist david helfgott , has a movie so defiantly laid bare the lives of world-class musicians .

docs.text: in fact , if one were to watch these films together , it would almost certainly stand as a convincing argument that a life of music naturally leads to all varieties of social ills .

docs.text: yet hilary and jackie , the sophomore effort from director anand tucker , has something more to say -- it softly but strongly explores the complex relationships of sibling rivalry and love in a very compelling tale .

docs.text: emily watson and rachel griffiths are the leads in this tale , playing the sisters du pr ? .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: both musicians from childhood , hilary ( griffiths ) is renowned flutist while jacqueline ( watson ) is easily as skilled on the cello .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the two comepete for and win many honors as children and as young women , both together and seperate .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: their careers as musicians surpass and then bow to one another's , and although their lives take very different paths -- hilary settles down to marriage and a family while rachel skips across the globe on a world concert tour -- they are bound together by their deep family love .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the performances of watson and griffiths are excellent in style and substance .

docs.text: they contrast each other wonderfully , and while watson's portrayal of jackie du pr ? is at times eccentric and perhaps unsympathetic , both characters are charged with emotion .

docs.text: the frank cottrell boyce script , which is based on the book by hilary and piers du pr ? , brings a great deal of depth to these characters as well .

docs.text: the script is also to be commended for its well-polished dual nature .

docs.text: cottrell boyce adopts a style which one might expect to see in a mystery thriller ( which was in fact the case with david koepp and robert towne's script for mission : impossible ) and skillfully molds it to the story of two rising musicians on different courses to fame .

docs.text: the latter parts of his script are controversial to say the least , and the rather depressing ending takes the wind out of an envigorating story .

docs.text: nevertheless , hilary and jackie is a movie that reaches an upper echelon of contemporary cinema through solid fundamentals and is a decent watch all around .
